SOURCELONG:Unearthed Arcana - Realm Subclasses	SOURCESHORT:UA	SOURCEWEB:https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/dnd/ua	SOURCEDATE:2024-01																													
																																
###Block: Bard subclass																																
College of the Moon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.Bard Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The College of the Moon traces its origins to the ancient druidic circles of the Moonshae Isles, who entrusted the first Bards of this tradition with chronicling the stories of the islands and their people. Bards of this college draw from the isles' Fey magic and the primal power of the moonwells to bolster their allies, protect the natural world, and inspire their bardic works. Such works tend to be based on well-known Moonshae myths such as the whimsy of fairy pranksters, the viciousness of the Beast, and the mysteries of the moonwells.	KEY:Bard Subclass ~ College of the Moon																		ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Moonshae Folktales|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Primal Lorist|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Blessing of the Moonwells|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,6	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Bolstered Folktales|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,14					SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5	SOURCEPAGE:UA
																																
Moonshae Folktales	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	"DESC:As a Magic action, you can invoke the power of a folktale, imbuing yourself with primal magic until you use this feature again. When you use this feature, choose which of the following folktales you invoke; your choice gives you certain benefits while this magic is active. &nl; Tale of Life. You invoke a tale of vitality and thriving earth. When you restore Hit Points to a creature with a spell, you can expend a Bardic Inspiration die and increase the amount of Hit Points restored by a number equal to a roll of the Bardic Inspiration die. You can do this only once per turn. &nl; Tale of Gloam. You invoke a tale of mystery and secrets. When you use a Bonus Action to give a creature a Bardic Inspiration die, you can take the Disengage or Hide action as part of that Bonus Action. &nl; Tale of Mirth. You invoke a tale of merriment and fey guile. When an enemy you can see within 60 feet of yourself succeeds on a saving throw, you can take a Reaction to expend a Bardic Inspiration die. The creature then must roll the Bardic Inspiration die ansubtract the number rolled from the save's total, possibly causing the save to fail."	KEY:College of the Moon ~Moonshae Folktales																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Primal Lorist	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You learn Druidic and one cantrip from the Druid spell list. It counts as a Bard spell for you but doesn't count against the number of cantrips you know. Additionally, choose one of the following skills: Animal Handling, Insight, Medicine, Nature, Perception, or Survival. You have proficiency in that skill.	KEY:College of the Moon ~Primal Lore		DEFINE:DruidicLanguage|1				BONUS:VAR|DruidicLanguage|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Bard_Druidic_Cantrip|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Bard_Primal_Lorist_Skill|3					ABILITY:Language|AUTOMATIC|Druidic													SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Blessing of the Moonwell	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You always have the Moonbeam spell prepared. As a Bonus Action, you can cast Moonbeam without expending a spell slot. When you cast it using this feature, you glow faintly while you maintain Concentration on the spell. While glowing, you shed Dim Light out to 5 feet, and whenever a creature fails its saving throw against the effects of this Moonbeam, another creature of your choice that you can see within 60 feet of you regains 2d4 Hit Points. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 3+ spell slot (no action required).	KEY:College of the Moon ~Blessing of the Moonwell													SPELLS:Blessing of the Moonwell|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=BardLVL|Moonbeam													SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Bolstered Folktales	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The power of your Moonshae Folktales improves. When you use your Tale of Life or Tale of Mirth, you can roll 1d6 and use the number rolled in place of expending a Bardic Inspiration die, and when you use your Tale of Gloam, you can also teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see as part of that Bonus Action.	KEY:College of the Moon ~Bolstered Folktales																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
																																
### Primal Lorist Cantrips																																
Druidcraft	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		"DESC:Whispering to the spirits of nature, you create one of the following effects within range:&nl;- You create a tiny, harmless sensory effect that predicts what the weather will be at your location for the next 24 hours. The effect might manifest as a golden orb for clear skies, a cloud for rain, falling snowflakes for snow, and so on. This effect persists for 1 round.&nl;- You instantly make a flower blossom, a seed pod open, or a leaf bud bloom.&nl;- You create an instantaneous, harmless sensor effect, such as falling leaves, a puff of wind, the sound of a small animal, or the faint odor of skunk. The effect must fit in a 5-foot cube.&nl;- You instantly light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire."	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Druidcraft																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Druidcraft,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Druidcraft								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Elementalism	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip			KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Elementalism																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Elementalism,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Elementalism								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Guidance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one ability check of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the ability check. The spell then ends.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Guidance																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Guidance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Guidance								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Mending	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as a broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn cloak, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it. leaving no trace of the former damage. This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Mending																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mending,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Mending								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Message	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You point your finger toward a creature within range and whisper a message. The target (and only the target) hears the message and can reply in a whisper that only you can hear. You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know it is beyond the barrier. Magical silence. 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell. The spell doesn't have to follow a straight line and can travel freely around corners or through openings.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Message																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Message,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Message								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Poison Spray	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 1d12 poison damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d12 when you reach 5th level (2d12), 11th level (3d12), and 17th level (4d12).	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Poison Spray																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Poison Spray,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Poison Spray								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Produce Flame	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		"DESC:A flicking flame appears in our hand. The flame remains there for the duration and harms neither you nor your equipment. The flame sheds bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. The spell ends if you dismiss it as an action or if you cast it again.&nl;You can also attack with the flame, although doing so ends the spell. When you cast this spell, or as an action on a later turn, you can hurl the flame at a creature within 30 feet of you. Make a ranged spell attack. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 fire damage.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8)."	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Produce Flame																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Produce Flame,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Produce Flame								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Resistance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one saving throw of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the saving throw. The spell then ends.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Resistance																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Resistance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Resistance								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Shillelagh	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:The wood of a club or quarterstaff you are holding is imbued with nature's power. For the duration, you can use your spellcasting ability instead of Streangth for the attack and damage rolls of melee attacks using that weapon, and the weapon's damage die becomes a d8. The weapon also becomes magical, if it isn't already. The spell ends if you cast it again or if you let go of the weapon.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Shillelagh																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Shillelagh,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Shillelagh								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Spare the Dying	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You touch a living creature that has 0 hit points. The creature becomes stable. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Spare the Dying																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Spare the Dying,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Spare the Dying								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Starry Wisp	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip			KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Starry Wisp																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Starry Wisp,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Starry Wisp								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Thunderclap	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip			KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Thunderclap																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thunderclap,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Thunderclap								SOURCEPAGE:UA
Thorn Whip	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		"DESC:You create a long, vine-like whip covered in thorns that lashes out at your command toward a creature in range. Make a melee spell attack against the target. If the attack hits, the creature takes 1d6 piercing damage, and if the creature is Large or smaller, you pull the creature up to 10 feet closer to you.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th elvel (3d6), and 17th level (4d6)."	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Thorn Whip																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thorn Whip,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Thorn Whip								SOURCEPAGE:UA
																																
###Block: Cleric Subclass																																
Knowledge Domain	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Cleric Subclass.SpecialQuality.Divine Domain	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Knowledge Domain values learning and understanding above all. Clerics who tap into this domain study esoteric lore, collect old tomes, delve into the secret places of the earth, and examine the process of the mind itself. Gods of knowledge vary from masters of arcane magic to patrons of craft and invention. To them, knowledge is more valuable than material wealth, and the desire to learn is an act of worship. Libraries, universities, and other institutions dedicated to education also draw on the power of the Knowledge Domain. On Faerùn, Clerics of the Knowledge Domain worship deities of learning and ingenuity like Oghma and Gond. Other powerful deities-such as Asmodeus, Mystra, Savras, and Jergal-also count Clerics of the Knowledge Domain among their devotees, as do less-common divinities like Deneir, the Scribe of Oghma, and Azuth, servant of Mystra.	KEY:Cleric Subclass ~ Knowledge Domain																		ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Blessing of Knowledge|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,3	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Knowledge Domain Spells|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,3	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Mind Magic|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,3	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Unfettered Mind|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,6	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Divine Foreknowledge|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,17				SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5	SOURCEPAGE:UA
																																
Blessing of Knowledge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality		DESC:You gain proficiency with one type of Artisan's Tools of your choice and in two of the following skills of your choice: Arcana, History, Nature, or Religion. You have Expertise in those two skills.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Blessing of Knowledge						BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Artisan's Tools Proficiency|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Expertise|2																			SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Knowledge Domain Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Cleric level specified in the Knowledge Domain Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Knowledge Domain Spells														SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Command|Comprehend Languages|Detect Magic|Detect Thoughts|Identify|Mind Spike|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,3	SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Dispel Magic|Nondetection|Tongues|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,5	SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Arcane Eye|Banishment|Confusion|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,7	SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Legend Lore|Scrying|Synaptic Static|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Mind Magic	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to manifest your magical knowledge. Choose one spell from the Knowledge Domain Spells table that you have prepared. As part of that action, you cast that spell without expending a spell slot or needing Material components.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Mind Magic																										SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Unfettered Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain telepathy out to 60 feet. When you use this telepathy, you can simultaneously contact a number of creatures equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of one). Additionally, if your total for an Intelligence check is lower than your Wisdom score, you can use that score in place of the total.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Unfettered Mind						BONUS:VAR|TelepathyRage|60																				SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Divine Foreknowledge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you magically expand your mind to the possibilities of the future. For 1 hour, you have Advantage on D20 Tests. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of this feature by expending a level 6+ spell slot (no action required).	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Divine Foreknowledge																										SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5e	SOURCEPAGE:UA
																																
###Block Figther Subclass																																
Purple Dragon Knight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Fighter Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Purple Dragon Knights are paragons of valor and leadership who partner with amethyst dragons. Such knights aspire to protect the innocent and rally fellow adventurers to the causes of justice and freedom. Although the Purple Dragons were originally founded in Cormyr, new recruits are enlisted from any realms where chivalry is in abundance, including the Silver Marches, Damara, and Chessenta. Characters with this subclass are special among the order. Unlike most Purple Dragons, who partner with amethyst dragons who've already reached adulthood, a Purple Dragon Knight character psionically bonds with an amethyst dragon hatchling. This bond irrevocably transforms both dragon and knight, allowing the dragon to grow in strength alongside its partner knight.	KEY:Fighter Subclass ~ Purple Dragon Knight																		ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Knightly Envoy|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Purple Dragon companion|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Dragon Raider|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,7	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Rallying Surge|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,10	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Amethyst Pinnacle|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,15	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Enduring Commander|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f5	SOURCEPAGE:UA
																																
Knightly Envoy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You learn one language of your choice, which you choose from the language tables in the Player's Handbook. Additionally, you can cast the Comprehend Languages spell but only as a Ritual. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for it.	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Knightly Envoy						BONUS:VAR|POOL_Language|1							SPELLS:Kniglthy Envoy|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=FighterLVL|Comprehend Language ~ Ritual,SpellDC_INT													SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Purple Dragon Companion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You are bonded with an amethyst dragon hatchling that serves as your purple dragon companion and uses the Purple Dragon Companion stat block. The purple dragon is Friendly to you and your allies and obeys your commands. &nl; The Dragon in Combat. In combat, the dragon acts during your turn. It can move and use its Reaction on its own, but the only action it takes is the Dodge action unless you take a Bonus Action to command it to take an action in its stat block or some other action. If you have the Incapacitated condition, the dragon acts on its own and isn't limited to the Dodge action. &nl; Resurrecting the Dragon. If the dragon companion has died within the last hour, you can take a Magic action to touch the dragon and expend a use of your Second Wind. The dragon returns to life after 1 minute with all its Hit Points restored. Otherwise, you can perform a 1-hour ceremony to resurrect the dragon; this ceremony can be performed as part of a Short or Long Rest.	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Purple Dragon Companion						BONUS:VAR|PurpleDragonCompanionLVL|FighterLVL							ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Companion													SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Dragon Rider	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You and your purple dragon gain the following benefits. &nl; Dragon Mount. The dragon grows to Medium size. You can use the dragon as a mount if you are Medium or smaller, but while you're riding it, the dragon falls at the end of a turn if it's airborne and the only thing holding it aloft is its Fly Speed. It takes you only 5 feet of movement to mount or dismount the dragon. &nl; Improved Gravity Breath. The dragon's Gravity Breath becomes a 30-foot Cone. When a creature fails its saving throw against that Gravity Breath, the creature also takes 2d6 Force damage. &nl; Shared Second Wind. When you use your Second Wind to regain Hit Points, the dragon also regains Hit Points equal to 1d6 plus your Fighter level, and it regains one use of its Gravity Breath.	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Dragon Rider																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Rallying Surge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you use your Action Surge, you can choose up to three allies within a 30-foot Emanation originating from you. Each ally can take a Reaction to use one of the following options. &nl; Advance. The ally makes one attack with a weapon or an Unarmed Strike. If your purple dragon is one of the allies using Advance, the dragon can make one Rend attack. &nl; Retreat. The ally moves up to half its Speed without provoking Opportunity Attacks.	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Rallying Surge																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Amethyst Pinnacle	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You and your purple dragon gain the following benefits. &nl; Superior Mount. The purple dragon grows to Large size, and both its Speed and its Fly Speed increase to 40 feet. Additionally, the dragon no longer falls at the end of a turn if airborne while you're riding it. &nl; Tandem Attack. When you take the Attack action on your turn, you can forego one of your attacks to command the dragon to make one Rend attack. Alternatively, you can forego two of your attacks to command the dragon to use Gravity Breath.	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Amethyst Pinnacle																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1e	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Enduring Commander	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You and your purple dragon have Resistance to Force and Psychic damage.	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Enduring Commander																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1f	SOURCEPAGE:UA

###Block Paladin Subclass																																
Oath of the Noble Genie	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Paladin Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Paladins sworn to the Oath of the Noble Genies revere the forces of the Elemental Planes. Through taking this oath, Paladins draw power from the four different types of genies-dao, masters of earth; djinn, masters of air; efreet, masters of fire; and marids, masters of water to create splendid and destructive displays of elemental might. On Faerûn, many Paladins who swear this oath hail from Calimshan, a land rife with genie-kind. Despite their strong local ties, these Calishite Paladins often undertake quests that take them all over the Realms and across the multiverse— including, naturally, the Elemental Planes. These paladins share the following tenets: &nl; *  Beget creation with destruction. &nl; *  Lead with splendor and grace. &nl; *  Respect the elements, and fear their wrath.	KEY:Paladin Subclass ~ Oath of the Noble Genie																		ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Elemental Smite|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Genie Spells|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Genie's Splendor|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Aura of Elemental Shielding|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,7	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Elemental Rebuke|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,15	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Noble Scion|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,20				SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g5	SOURCEPAGE:UA

Elemental Smite	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Noble Genie.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Immediately after you cast Divine Smite, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity and invoke one of the following effects. Dao's Crush. The target has the Grappled condition (escape DC equal to your spell save DC). While Grappled, the target has the Restrained condition. &nl; Djinni's Escape. You teleport to an unoccupied space you can see within 30 feet of yourself and take on a mist-like form, which lasts until the end of your next turn. While in this form, you have Immunity to the Grappled, Prone, and Restrained conditions. &nl; Efreeti's Fury. The target takes an extra 2d4 Fire damage. &nl; Marid's Surge. The target and each creature of your choice in a 10-foot Emanation originating from you makes a Strength saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the creature is pushed 15 feet straight away from you and has the Prone condition.	KEY:Oath of Noble Genie ~ Elemental Smite																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Genie Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Noble Genie.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The magic of your oath ensures you always have certain spells ready; when you reach a Paladin level specified in the Oath of Noble Genie Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Oath of Noble Genie ~ Genie Spells														SPELLS:Genie Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=PaladinLVL|Chromatic Orb|Elementalism,Thunderous Smite|PREVARGTEQ:PaladinLVL,3	SPELLS:Genie Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=PaladinLVL|Mirror Image|Phantasmal Force|PREVARGTEQ:PaladinLVL,5	SPELLS:Genie Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=PaladinLVL|Fly|Gaseous Form|PREVARGTEQ:PaladinLVL,9	SPELLS:Genie Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=PaladinLVL|Conjure Minor Elementals|Summon Elemental|PREVARGTEQ:PaladinLVL,13	SPELLS:Genie spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=PaladinLVL|Banishing smite|Contect Other Plane|PREVARGTEQ:PaladinLVL,17								SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g5b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Genie's Splendor	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Noble Genie.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you aren't wearing Medium or Heavy armor, you gain a bonus to your AC equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of +1). You also gain proficiency in one of the following skills of your choice: Acrobatics, Intimidation, Performance, or Persuasion.	KEY:Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Genie's Splendor					BONUS:COMBAT|AC|max(CHA,1)|!PREEQUIP:2,TYPE=Armor.Heavy,TYPE=Armor.Medium	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Paladin_Genie_Splendor_Skill|1																				SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g5c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Aura of Elemental Shielding	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Noble Genie.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose one of the following damage types: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Thunder damage. You and your allies have Resistance to that damage type while in your Aura of Protection. At the start of each of your turns, you can change the damage type affected by this feature to one of the other listed options (no action required).	KEY:Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Genie's Splendor																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g5d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Elemental Rebuke	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Noble Genie.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you are hit by an attack roll, you can take a Reaction to halve the attack's damage against yourself (round down) and force the attacker to make a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the attacker takes damage equal to 4d10 plus your Charisma modifier; the damage is one of the following types (your choice): Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Thunder. On a successful save, the attacker takes half as much damage. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Elemental Rebuke																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g5e	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Noble Scion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Noble Genie.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you gain the benefits below for 10 minutes or until you end them (no action required). Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 5 spell slot (no action required). &nl; Flight. You have a Fly Speed of 60 feet and can hover. &nl; Minor Wish. When you or an ally in your Aura of Protection fails a D20 Test, you can take a Reaction to make the D20 Test succeed instead.	KEY:Oath of the Noble Genie ~ Noble Scion																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g5f	SOURCEPAGE:UA

###Block Ranger Subclass																																
Winter Walker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Ranger Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Winter Walkers hone their craft in the bleak and frozen wilds of places like Icewind Dale. Rimed with ice, these ruthless Rangers hunt the monsters that haunt arctic wastelands, eventually becoming frigid terrors themselves. More so than any other Rangers of Icewind Dale, Winter Walkers are known to be well versed in the paranormal phenomena specific to the realm, including the latent magic of fallen Netherese cities, endemic monsters like yetis and crag cats, and the rising threat of Underdark invaders. In exchange for their cold pragmatism, terrifying magic, and mastery of the region, these Winter Walkers are regarded with equal parts respect and fear. Ten-Towns citizens say that it is Winter Walkers’ frequent exposure to malignant entities that gives them their fearsome powers. Many Reghed nomads, on the other hand, believe that nature spirits bestow Winter Walkers with a unique curse.	KEY:Ranger Subclass ~ Winter Walker																		ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Winter Walker ~ Frigid Explorer|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Winter Walker ~ Hunter's Rime|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Winter Walker ~ Winter Walker Spells|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Winter Walker ~ Fortifying Soul|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,7	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Winter Walker ~ Chilling Retribution|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,11	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Winter Walker ~ Frozen Haunt|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,15				SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f5	SOURCEPAGE:UA

Frigid Explorer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Winter Walker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Frost Resistance. You have Resistance to Cold damage. &nl; Polar Strikes. When you hit a creature with a weapon, you can deal an extra 1d4 Cold damage to the target, which can take this extra damage only once per turn. This extra damage ignores Resistance to Cold damage. When you reach Ranger level 11, this extra damage increases to 1d6.	KEY:Winter Walker ~ Frigid Explorer																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Hunter's Rime	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Winter Walker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Ice rimes you and your prey, protecting you and slowing them. When you cast Hunter’s Mark, you gain Temporary Hit Points equal to 1d10 plus your Ranger level. Additionally, while a creature is marked by your Hunter’s Mark, it can’t take the Disengage action.	KEY:Winter Walker ~ Hunter's Rime																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f5b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Winter Walker Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Winter Walker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Ranger level specified in the Winter Walker Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Winter Walker ~ winter Walker Spells														SPELLS:Winter Walker Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RangerLVL|Ice Knife|PREVARGTEQ:RangerLVL,3	SPELLS:Winter Walker Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RangerLVL|Pass Without Trace|PREVARGTEQ:RangerLVL,5	SPELLS:Winter Walker Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RangerLVL|Remove Curse|PREVARGTEQ:RangerLVL,9	SPELLS:Winter Walker Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RangerLVL|Ice Storm|PREVARGTEQ:RangerLVL,13	SPELLS:Winter Walker Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RangerLVL|Cone of Cold|PREVARGTEQ:RangerLVL,17								SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f5c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Fortifying Soul	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Winter Walker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your experience surviving harrowing environments allows you to bolster your allies in addition to yourself. When you finish a Short Rest, you can choose a number of creatures you can see equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of one). A chosen creature regains Hit Points equal to 1d10 plus your Ranger level and has Advantage on saving throws to avoid or end the Frightened condition for 1 hour. Once you use this feature, you can’t use it again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Winter Walker ~ Frigid Explorer																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f5d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Chilling Retribution	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Winter Walker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a creature hits you with an attack roll, you can take a Reaction to force the creature to make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the target has the Frightened condition until the end of your next turn. While Frightened, a target’s Speed is reduced to 0 feet. You can use this Reaction a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Winter Walker ~ Chilling Retribution																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f5e	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Frozen Haunt	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Winter Walker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast Hunter’s Mark, you can adopt a ghostly, snowy form. This form lasts until the spell ends, and while you are in this form, you gain the following benefits. Once you use this feature, you can’t use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend a level 4+ spell slot (no action required). &nl; Frozen Soul. You have Immunity to Cold damage. When you first adopt this form and at the start of each of your subsequent turns, each creature of your choice in a 15-foot Emanation originating from you takes 2d4 Cold damage. &nl; Partially Incorporeal. You have Immunity to the Grappled, Prone, and Restrained conditions. You can move through creatures and objects as if they were Difficult Terrain, but you take 1d10 Force damage if you end your turn inside a creature or an object. If the form ends while you are inside a creature or an object, you are shunted to the nearest unoccupied space.	KEY:Winter Walker ~ Frozen Haunt																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f5f	SOURCEPAGE:UA

###Block Rogue Subclass																																
Scion of the Three	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Rogue Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A Scion of the Three draws power from a group of malevolent gods known as the Dead Three: Bane, deity of tyranny; Bhaal, deity of violence and murder; and Myrkul, deity of death. While some Rogues of this subclass pledge themselves ardently to those three macabre gods, others find themselves thrust on this path by a curse. Either way, a scion’s power manifests as various occult gifts, as well as an uncanny talent for striking and terrifying foes. Scions of the Three are most common in Baldur’s Gate, where the Dead Three have long competed for influence over mortal hearts. Underground cults to Bane, Bhaal, and Myrkul often count Scions of the Three among their most useful agents. Outside Baldur’s Gate, secular thieves’ guilds such as the Shadow Thieves of Amn or Xanathar’s guild in Waterdeep might cautiously call on a Scion of the Three to undertake an especially violent contract.	KEY:Rogue Subclass ~ Scion of the Three																		ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Scion of the Three ~ Bloodthirst|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Scion of the Three ~ Dread Alliance|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Scion of the Three ~ Strike Fear|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,9	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Scion of the Three ~ Aura of Malevolence|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,13	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Scion of the Three ~ Dread Incarnate|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,17					SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6	SOURCEPAGE:UA

Bloodthirst	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Scion of the Three.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If your Sneak Attack hits a Bloodied creature, the target takes extra damage of the weapon’s type equal to half your Rogue level (round up). In addition, when an enemy you can see is reduced to 0 Hit Points, you can take a Reaction and teleport to an unoccupied space you can see within 30 feet of yourself. You can then make one melee attack. You can use this Reaction a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Bloodthirst																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Dread Allegiance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Scion of the Three.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose one of the Dead Three: Bane, Bhaal, or Myrkul. You gain Resistance to one type of damage and the ability to cast a cantrip, as detailed in the table below; Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for this cantrip. When you finish a Long Rest, you can change your choice.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Dread Allegiance						BONUS:VAR|POOL_Dread_Allegiance|1																				SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Strike Fear	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Scion of the Three.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the following Cunning Strike option. &nl; Terrify (Cost: 1d6). The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw, or it has the Frightened condition for 1 minute. The Frightened target repeats the save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Strike Fear																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Aura of Malevolence	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Scion of the Three.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You radiate malignant power associated with one of the Dead Three. At the start of each of your turns, each creature of your choice within a 10-foot Emanation originating from you takes damage equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of 1); the damage type is the same as the damage Resistance granted by your choice in the Dread Allegiance feature. Damage dealt by this aura ignores Resistance. The aura is inactive while you have the Incapacitated condition.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Aura of Malevolence																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Dread Incarnate	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Scion of the Three.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the following benefits. &nl; Battle Tyrant. You have Advantage on attack rolls against any creature with the Frightened condition. &nl; Murderous Intent. When you roll for your Sneak Attack damage, you can treat a roll of a 1 or 2 on the die as a 3.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Dread Incarnate																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6e	SOURCEPAGE:UA

Bane	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:DreadAlliance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Psychic.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Dread Alliance ~ Bane													SPELLS:Dread Alliance|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RogueLVL|Minor Illusion,SpellDC_INT													SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6b1	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Bhaal	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:DreadAlliance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Poison.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Dread Alliance ~ Bhaal													SPELLS:Dread Alliance|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RogueLVL|Blade Ward,SpellDC_INT													SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6b2	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Myrkul	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:DreadAlliance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Necrotic.	KEY:Scion of the Three ~ Dread Alliance ~ Myrkul													SPELLS:Dread Alliance|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=RogueLVL|Chill Touch,SpellDC_INT													SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f6b3	SOURCEPAGE:UA

###Block Sorcerer Subclass																																
Spellfire Sorcery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Sorcerer Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your innate power stems from the source of magic itself: the Weave. This connection manifests as a rare ability known as spellfire, and you surge with radiant bursts of this raw magic. Your talent with spellfire allows you to heal allies, sear enemies, and absorb powerful spells. Wielders of spellfire tend to be adventurous souls with penchants for wandering. Many travel between cosmopolitan settlements, such as those along the Sword Coast, and wield their magic in service of the common good. Others prioritize the realization of their own strange powers by roaming equally strange lands, from the magic-blasted wastes of the Anauroch Desert to the god-touched wilds of the Old Empires. Wherever they go in the Realms, spellfire Sorcerers are often courted by factions with interests in the arcane arts, such as the Harpers and the Cult of the Dragon.	KEY:Sorcerer Subclass ~ Spellfire Sorcery																		ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Spellfire Sorcery ~ Spellfire Burst|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Spellfire Sorcery ~ Spellfire Spells|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Spellfire Sorcery ~ Absorb Spells|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,6	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Spellfire Sorcery ~ Honed Spellfire|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,14	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Spellfire Sorcery ~ Crown of Spellfire|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,18					SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f5	SOURCEPAGE:UA

Spellfire Burst	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Spellfire Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you spend at least 1 Sorcery Point as part of the Magic action or a Bonus Action on your turn, you can unleash one of the following magical effects of your choice. You can do so only once per turn. &nl; Bolstering Flames. You or one creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself gains Temporary Hit Points equal to 1d4 plus your Charisma modifier. &nl; Radiant Fire. One creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC or take 1d6 Fire or Radiant damage (your choice).	KEY:Spellfire Sorcery ~ Spellfire Burst																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Spellfire Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Spellfire Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Sorcerer level specified in the Spellfire Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Spellfire Sorcery ~ Spellfire Spells														SPELLS:Spellfire Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Cure Wounds|Guiding Bolt|Lesser Restorarion|Scorching Ray|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,3	SPELLS:Spellfire Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Aura of Vitality|Dispel Magic|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,5	SPELLS:Spellfire Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Fire Shield|Wall of Fire|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,7	SPELLS:Spellfire Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Greater Restoration|Flame Strike|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f5b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Absorb Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Spellfire Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You always have Counterspell prepared. Additionally, whenever a target fails the saving throw against a Counterspell you cast, you regain 1d4 Sorcery Points.	KEY:Spellfire Sorcery ~ Absorb Spells														SPELLS:Absorb Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Counterspell												SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f5c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Honed spellfire	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Spellfire Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Spellfire Burst improves. You add your Sorcerer level to the Temporary Hit Points gained from Bolstering Flames, and the 1d6 of Radiant Fire increases to 3d6.	KEY:Spellfire Sorcery ~ Honed Spellfire																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f5d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Crown of Spellfire	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Spellfire Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you gain the following benefits for 1 minute. Once you use this Bonus Action, you can’t use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you spend 7 Sorcery Points (no action required) to restore your use of it. &nl; Burning Life Force. Once per turn when you are hit by an attack roll, you cn expend a number of Hit Dice, up to a maximum equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one). Roll the expended dice and reduce the amount of damage from that attack equal to the total rolled plus your Sorcerer level. &nl; Flight. You gain a Fly Speed of 60 feet and can hover. &nl; Spell Avoidance. When you’re subjected to a spell or magical effect that allows you to make a saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw and only half damage if you fail. You can’t use this benefit if you have the Incapacitated condition.	KEY:Spellfire Sorcery ~ Spellfire Burst																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f5e	SOURCEPAGE:UA

###Block Wizard Subclass																																
Bladesinger	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Wizard Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Bladesingers master a tradition of wizardry that incorporates swordplay and dance. In combat, a Bladesinger uses a series of intricate, elegant maneuvers that fend off harm and allow the Bladesinger to channel magic into devastating attacks and a cunning defense. Many who have observed a Bladesinger at work remember the display as one of the more beautiful experiences in their life, a glorious dance accompanied by a singing blade. Bladesinging is strongly associated with the ancient elven societies that first mastered the art and coined the term. Even today, most Bladesingers still hail from old elven realms, such as Cormanthyr, or from non-elven societies that share land and history with elves, such as the Silver Marches. Wherever they hail from, Bladesingers are known for taking their talents all across the Realms in order to help common people and perform heroic deeds. Few communities greet the arrival of a Bladesinger as anything but a good omen.	KEY:Wizard Subclass ~ Bladesinger																		ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinger ~ Bladesong|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinger ~ Training in War and Song|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinger ~ Extra Attack|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,6	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinger ~ Song of Defense|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,10	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinger ~ Song of Victory|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,14					SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e5	SOURCEPAGE:UA

Bladesong	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Bladesinger.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you invoke an elven magic called the Bladesong, provided you aren’t wearing armor or using a Shield. ©2025 Wizards of the Coast LLC 9 The Bladesong lasts for 1 minute and ends early if you have the Incapacitated condition, if you don armor or a Shield, or if you use two hands to make an attack with a weapon. You can dismiss the Bladesong at any time (no action required). While the Bladesong is active, you gain the following benefits. You can invoke the Bladesong a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Agility. You gain a bonus to your AC equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of +1), and your Speed increases by 10 feet. &nl; Bladework. Whenever you attack with a weapon with which you have proficiency, you can use your Intelligence modifier for the attack and damage rolls instead of using Strength or Dexterity. &nl; Focus. When you make a Constitution saving throw to maintain Concentration, you can add your Intelligence modifier to the total.	KEY:Bladesinger ~ Bladesong																										SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Training in War and Song	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Bladesinger.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain proficiency with all Melee Martial weapons that don’t have the Two-Handed or Heavy property. You can use a Melee weapon with which you have proficiency as a Spellcasting Focus for your Wizard spells. You also gain proficiency in one of the following skills of your choice: Acrobatics, Athletics, Performance, or Persuasion.	KEY:Bladesinger ~ Bladesong						BONUS:VAR|POOL_Bladesinger_Skill|1								ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=WeaponProfBladesinger												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e5b	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Bladesinger.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn. Moreover, you can cast one of your Wizard cantrips that has a casting time of an action in place of one of those attacks.	KEY:Bladesinger ~ Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 1								SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e5c	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Song of Defense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Bladesinger.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take damage while your Bladesong is active, you can take a Reaction to expend one spell slot and reduce the damage taken by an amount equal to five times the spell slot’s level.	KEY:Bladesinger ~ Song of Defense																										SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e5d	SOURCEPAGE:UA
Song of Victory	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Bladesinger.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:After you cast a spell that has a casting time of an action, you can make one attack with a weapon as a Bonus Action.	KEY:Bladesinger ~ Song of Victory																										SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e5e	SOURCEPAGE:UA
